:Guerrilla wars]]\n[[Category:History of Nepal (1951\u20132008)]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Nepal]]\n[[Category:Maoism in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Politics of Nepal]]\n[[Category:Communism-based civil wars]]\n[[Category:Nepalese democracy movements]]\n[[Category:20th century in Nepal]]\n[[Category:2000s in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Wars involving India]]\n[[Category:21st-century rebellions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1996\u20132006 civil war between the Nepalese government and a communist party}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Expert needed|date=May 2015}}\n{{POV check|date=January 2009}}\n{{More citations needed|date=May 2015}}}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict          = Nepalese Civil War\n| image             = Ktm2006-malema.JPG\n| image_size        = 300px\n| caption           = Communist [[graffiti]] in [[Kathmandu]]. It reads: \"Long Live [[Marxism\u2013Leninism\u2013Maoism\u2013Prachanda Path|Marxism-Leninism-Maoism and Prachanda Path]]!\"\n| date              = 13 February 1996 \u2013 21 November 2006<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=13|year1=1996|month2=11|day2=21|year2=2006}})\n| place             = [[Nepal]]\n| casus             = [[Maoist]] opposition to the Nepali state\n| result            = [[Comprehensive Peace Accord]]\n* [[2008 Nepalese Constituent Assembly election|Constituent Assembly election]] held\n* Entry of [[Communist Party of Nepal (Maoist Centre)|Maoists]] into [[Politics of Nepal|mainstream politics]]\n* End of [[Monarchy of Nepal|240-year-long monarchy]]\n| combatant1        = {{flagicon|Nepal}} [[Kingdom of Nepal]]<br /> {{small|([[Politics of Nepal|Government of Nepal]])}}<br>\n* [[Royal Nepalese Army]]\n'''Supported by: '''<br />{{flagicon|United States}} [[United States]]<ref name=\"reliefweb\">{{Cite web|url=https://reliefweb.int/report/nepal/nepals-maoist-cauldron-draws-foreign-powers-closer|title=Nepal's Maoist cauldron draws foreign powers closer|last=Miglani|first=Sanjeev|date=18 August 2003|publis